.TH "fsl_rio_config_write" 9 "fsl_rio_config_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsl_rio_config_write \- Generate a MPC85xx write maintenance transaction
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsl_rio_config_write
.BI "(struct rio_mport *mport "  ","
.BI "int index "  ","
.BI "u16 destid "  ","
.BI "u8 hopcount "  ","
.BI "u32 offset "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "u32 val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mport" 12
RapidIO master port info
.IP "index" 12
ID of RapdiIO interface
.IP "destid" 12
Destination ID of transaction
.IP "hopcount" 12
Number of hops to target device
.IP "offset" 12
Offset into configuration space
.IP "len" 12
Length (in bytes) of the maintenance transaction
.IP "val" 12
Value to be written
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Generates an MPC85xx write maintenance transaction. Returns 0 on
success or -EINVAL on failure.
